ODIFYING TITLE 44, UNITED STATES CODE' THE NATIONAL PUBLICATIONS ACT OF1980.CONTRIBUTION TO A THEMATIC ISSUE DEVOTED TO US FEDERAL GOVERNMENT PRINTING ANDPUBLISHING REFORM. THE US GOVERNMENT PRINTING OFFICE HAS ELUDED FOR A NUMBEROF YEARS ATTEMPTS TO INSTALL MODERN MANAGEMENT TECHNIQUES FOR THE PRINTING,BINDING, AND DISTRIBUTION OF FEDERAL GOVERNMENT PUBLICATIONS. IN 1978 ACONCERTED EFFORT AT PRINTING REFORM WAS INITIATED IN CONGRESS, RESULTING INTHE NATIONAL PUBLICATIONS ACT OF 1980. PRESENTS AN OVERVIEW OF THE GENERALCONDITIONS WHICH PROMPTED THE REFORM LEGISLATION, ITS PREPARATION, AND THESUBSTANCE OF ITS PROVISIONS